The Department of State Security (DSS) will review all cases of unlawful detentions and human right abuses, the Acting Director General of the agency, Mr. Matthew Seiyefa has said. Seiyefa, in his maiden press conference on Thursday, said the protection of national interest will be top of the agancy's agenda henceforth. He also assured that the DSS will collaborate with all other agencies to ensure security in the country. The new DSS boss said the political atmosphere will not influence the agency's work. Deatails later...